<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="729" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d729">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Herbert</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Navy
                                        Department</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-14"><hi rend="italic">January 14,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of the Department of State’s communication of the 2d instant,
                            and to advise you that a copy thereof has been transmitted to the
                            commander-in-chief of the United States naval force on the European
                            station for his guidance.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">H. A. Herbert</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Secretary.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>